32:49.800 --> 32:51.097
You'll testify to this?

32:51.130 --> 32:53.223
Of course. Usual fee.

32:53.270 --> 32:56.091
WILL:
The problem is,
it's not a good story.

32:56.140 --> 32:58.301
It's just a freak accident.

32:58.340 --> 32:59.602
There are no villains.

32:59.640 --> 33:01.005
But if it's true...

33:01.040 --> 33:03.179
But it doesn't
sound true.

33:03.210 --> 33:05.041
The prosecution's story sounds
like the truth--

33:05.080 --> 33:07.378
there's a villain: Bianca,
there's a motive: jealousy.

33:07.410 --> 33:09.219
This story just says
there's no rhyme or reason.

33:09.250 --> 33:10.672
Everything's random.

33:10.720 --> 33:12.745
Well, we're not trying
to teach a lesson.

33:12.790 --> 33:13.779
Just win a verdict.
There's another problem.

33:13.820 --> 33:16.152
We've already set our story
that Josh did it.

33:16.190 --> 33:18.385
Even our own ballistics expert
supported that.

33:18.430 --> 33:20.751
Right. We'd have to contradict
our own ballistics expert.

33:20.790 --> 33:22.223
Well, there's
an another way

33:22.260 --> 33:24.592
to settle this:
ask the client.

33:29.100 --> 33:31.307
So that's what happened?

33:31.340 --> 33:33.763
That's what our ballistics
expert said happened.

33:33.810 --> 33:36.301
So, I don't know. Do we put this
new evidence on the stand

33:36.340 --> 33:38.342
or not?
Which is smarter?

33:38.380 --> 33:39.802
Well, that's up
for discussion.

33:39.850 --> 33:43.775
CARY:
Our worry is we tried one
defense with the jury,

33:43.820 --> 33:46.687
and now if we try another,
we might do two things:

33:46.720 --> 33:47.948
undercut our credibility
and hurt our chances

33:47.990 --> 33:51.255
if the jury was believing our
first defense, that Josh did it.

33:51.290 --> 33:53.155
So what should I do?

33:55.630 --> 33:56.790
You go with the truth.

33:56.830 --> 34:00.220
The truth has the advantage of
being true, and on some level,

34:00.270 --> 34:03.068
the truth is always
more believable.

34:03.100 --> 34:06.263
Then that's what
we go with, the truth.

34:06.310 --> 34:09.074
And you believe
the gunshot was self-inflicted?

34:09.110 --> 34:10.634
Well, I don't believe.

34:10.680 --> 34:12.272
The science points there.

34:12.310 --> 34:14.847
The gunshot was accidentally
self-inflicted.

34:14.880 --> 34:16.245
Thank you, Mr. McVeigh.

34:16.280 --> 34:17.042
No problem.

34:17.080 --> 34:19.548
MATAN:
As you said, Mr. McVeigh,

34:19.590 --> 34:23.219
you originally didn't want
to testify in this case?

34:23.260 --> 34:26.184
Yes. I thought
Miss Price was guilty.
Right.

34:26.230 --> 34:29.358
Then two days ago
you had an epiphany?

34:29.400 --> 34:33.097
Well, if by epiphany you mean
a new piece of evidence--

34:33.130 --> 34:35.132
this jacket with bloodstain
and GSR--

34:35.170 --> 34:37.468
then yes,
I did have that.

34:37.500 --> 34:39.138
A change of heart?

34:39.170 --> 34:42.071
Not my choice of words,
but I won't object to 'em.

34:44.250 --> 34:46.172
You're staying
at the Westin

34:46.210 --> 34:47.472
while you testify
in another case?

34:47.510 --> 34:49.148
Yes.

34:49.180 --> 34:50.112
This is a hotel

34:50.150 --> 34:52.414
where many prosecutors house
their witnesses?

34:52.450 --> 34:53.883
Yes, I believe that's true.

34:53.920 --> 34:56.286
It's a hotel where several
prosecutors observed you

34:56.320 --> 34:57.309
meeting with another lawyer.

34:57.360 --> 34:59.419
Is that a question?

34:59.460 --> 35:00.427
No.

35:00.460 --> 35:03.190
Here's the question:

35:03.230 --> 35:06.324
Two nights ago before you
magically changed your mind

35:06.370 --> 35:08.531
about this case, did you have
dinner with a partner

35:08.570 --> 35:11.630
from the law firm, Stern,
Lockhart & Gardner?

35:11.670 --> 35:12.602
Yes.
Objection!

35:12.640 --> 35:14.631
The question's been answered,
Mr. Gardner.

35:14.680 --> 35:16.773
Yes, Your Honor, I'm sorry, but
it was answered too quickly.

35:16.810 --> 35:19.199
Well let me overrule
just as qUIckly.

35:19.250 --> 35:23.846
And after this dinner,
the partner in question,

35:23.880 --> 35:24.847
Diane Lockhart,

35:24.890 --> 35:27.848
joined you in
your hotel room?

35:27.890 --> 35:30.415
Yes.

35:31.930 --> 35:34.353
MATAN:
And did you have
sexual relations?

35:34.400 --> 35:35.822
Objection, Your Honor!
How is this relevant?

35:35.860 --> 35:38.397
Well, I would imagine
that Mr. Brody would say

35:38.430 --> 35:41.729
that the witness's testimony
was bought these alleged

35:41.770 --> 35:44.238
sexual relations,
isn't that correct, Mr. Brody?

35:44.270 --> 35:45.259
It is, Your Honor.

35:45.310 --> 35:47.232
Well, Mr. Brody,
I will sustain

35:47.270 --> 35:49.272
Mr. Gardner's objections,

35:49.310 --> 35:51.198
but I don't think
you'll mind much

35:51.250 --> 35:54.219
because you just threw a stink
bomb into the lap of the jury,

35:54.250 --> 35:56.172
and now you're running
for cover.

35:56.220 --> 35:57.847
Your Honor,
this is an instance...

35:57.880 --> 35:59.211
And, Mr. Gardner, yes,

35:59.250 --> 36:01.218
I see the outrage on your face,

36:01.260 --> 36:04.286
which I might be more moved by
if you hadn't done

36:04.330 --> 36:06.525
the exact same thing with
Detective Burton's testimony.

36:06.560 --> 36:07.754
Excuse me,
Your Honor,

36:07.790 --> 36:09.951
with all clues respect...
Please, Your Honor...

36:10.000 --> 36:10.898
No, no, no.

36:10.930 --> 36:14.297
This one we're calling a draw,
gentlemen.

36:14.340 --> 36:17.195
You have both been playing
fast and loose

36:17.240 --> 36:19.708
with implications,
not facts, so we're gonna

36:19.740 --> 36:22.231
try and let justice
take care of itself.

36:22.280 --> 36:24.441
You have any more questions,
Mr. Brody?

36:24.480 --> 36:25.674
No, Your Honor,

36:25.710 --> 36:27.644
but we do request
a limiting instruction.

36:27.680 --> 36:30.376
Members of the jury,
in weighing

36:30.420 --> 36:33.844
Mr. McVeigh's testimony, you may
consider any potential bias

36:33.890 --> 36:39.385
in assessing the weight you want
to give to what he had to say.

36:41.730 --> 36:45.325
You know, I think
it's almost medieval.

36:45.370 --> 36:47.361
They toss us in here,
they lock the door,

36:47.400 --> 36:49.868
they throw a lot of
contradictory evidence at us,

36:49.900 --> 36:51.868
and then they expect us
to come up with a fair decision.

36:51.910 --> 36:53.468
